Definition: a radix numeration system in which the location of the decimal point is indicated by an exponent of the radix
Example: in the floating-point representation system, 0.0012 is represented as 0.12-2 where -2 is the exponent
Synonyms: floating-point_representation_system, mathematical_notation, a, radix, numeration, system, in, which, the, location, of, decimal, point, is, indicated, by, an, exponent, floating-point, representation, represented, as, -, where
Category: noun.communication
